ntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075809/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>For shorter travel XC and light trail bikes, their inline EDGE shocks get an EDGE Plus option that uses a larger air canister.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1.jpg\" alt=\"2022 sr suntour edge plus high volume inline rear shock for XC and light trail bikes\" width=\"2086\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1.jpg 2086w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1-297