/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1-1536x663.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075805/sr-suntour-Edge-Plus-XC-inline-rear-shock-2022-1-2048x884.jpg 2048w\"></a></p><p>This adds more volume, similar to what the Fox EVOL and Rockshox DebonAir options offer. The idea is to give these bikes a bit more cushioned feel when you don’t need or want a firm, pro-racing feel. Not sure if this is right for your bike? Check out our <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2014/08/14/suspension-setup-series-4-fix-your-ride-by-adjusting-air-volume/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Suspension Setup Series article</a> on air volume and how it affects your ride.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1.jpg\" alt=\"2022 SR Suntour Rux and Durolux enduro mountain bike suspension forks with 38mm stanchions\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1339\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1-297x249.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1-800x670.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075758/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-1-12