bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075801/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-3-120x79.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02075801/sr-suntour-38mm-stanchion-RUX-and-Durolux-MTB-forks-2022-3-768x505.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Up front, they’re offering new 38mm stanchion versions of their double-crown RUX fork and enduro racing Durolux forks. The forks will come with either their R2C2 or RC2 damping cartridges, with some markets only getting the latest RC2 option. Both also use the latest EQ Air spring design, which <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/06/sr-suntour-auron-trail-fork-gets-eq-air-spring-upgrade-for-smoother-quieter-squish/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">debuted on the Auron trail fork</a> earlier this year.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.srsuntour.us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>SRSuntour.us</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f205434fef60dee6aaa545270763b54ed8fbd5bb5ffb3a6e38e8fafe47736a90","category":"Cycling"}